        "style": "light",
        "decorator": "none",
        "content": "<p>To properly run eommerce projects of scale, it&#39;s essential to attract ecommerce professionals. The lack of deep ecommerce expertise often leads to the choice of a solution which doesn&rsquo;t fit the business. The lack of experience in planning and execution of agile implementation projects leads to long, unpredictable projects, lost funds, and, as a result - a very slow return on ROI.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>When software becomes&nbsp;an inhibitor instead of being a solution, the mid-market company loses a&nbsp;critical advantage, which helps to win larger competitors &ndash; the speed of change. As the result a company loses more and more market opportunities, cannot implement its strategy with the required velocity, and cannot act proactively - just because of a low platform adoption speed.</p>\n\n<p>Implementation budgets are often tight, and mid-market companies often don&rsquo;t have easily available resources (free cash flow). It means that every time the project goes over budget, management should either freeze the project until money is available or sacrifice other investments to allow project to continue. Both decisions are painful decisions which slow a company&#39;s growth.&nbsp;</p>\n",
